Question Description:

Develop a Java program to convert Meter between Centimeter 
and Kilometer. The Meter class includes a double value attribute, 
along with methods to perform conversions. Subclasses Centimeter 
and Kilometer extend Meter. In the Main class, users input a 
meter value, and the program converts and displays the value in 
the opposite unit.

Boilerplate Code:

import java.util.Scanner;
 class Meter { 
 double value; 
 public Meter(double value) { 
 this.value = value; 
 } 
 } 
 class Centimeter extends Meter { 
 //fill code 
 } 
 class Kilometer extends Meter { 
 //fill code 
 } 
 } 
 public class Main { 
 public static void main(String[] args) { 
 //fill your code here 
 } 
 }

Sample Input1:

Kilometer 200

Sample Output1:

Converted Unit :0.2 km

Sample Input2:

Centimeter 200

Sample Output2:

Converted Unit :20000.0 cm
